SUPERMON-NG USER CONFIGURATION DIRECTORY
========================================

This directory - user_files - houses ALL of the files that the Supermon-ng
user can configure. There are NO configurable files in the supermon-ng
directory. Do NOT change permissions of files.

ACTIVE CONFIGURATION FILES
--------------------------

authini.inc      - INI to user mapping configuration
authusers.inc    - Button to user permission mapping
allmon.ini       - The default Supermon-ng initialization file
global.inc       - User configuration settings
favini.inc       - Favorites INI file mapping configuration
favorites.ini    - Favorites button configuration
controlpanel.ini - Control Panel button configuration
privatenodes.txt - Private AllStar nodes list
background.jpg   - Header background image (symbolic link)

USER-SPECIFIC FILES (OPTIONAL)
------------------------------

You may create user-specific configuration files by replacing <username> 
with the actual login username:

<username>-allmon.ini        - User-specific allmon configuration
<username>-favorites.ini     - User-specific favorites configuration  
<username>-controlpanel.ini  - User-specific control panel configuration

EXAMPLE: For user "john", create:
- john-allmon.ini
- john-favorites.ini
- john-controlpanel.ini

CONFIGURATION MAPPING
---------------------

The following files control which configuration files are used for each user:

authini.inc      - Maps usernames to specific allmon.ini files
favini.inc       - Maps usernames to specific favorites.ini files
cntrlini.inc     - Maps usernames to specific controlpanel.ini files

If these mapping files don't exist, the default files are used for all users.

SECURITY NOTES
--------------

- Keep authusers.inc secure - it contains user permissions
- Regularly backup your configuration files
- Test configuration changes in a safe environment
- Use strong passwords for AMI connections

BACKGROUND IMAGE
---------------

Replace background.jpg with your own image by:
1. Place your image in this directory
2. Update the symbolic link: ln -sf your_image.jpg background.jpg

SUPPORT
-------

For configuration help, see the Supermon-ng documentation
or visit the AllStar Link community forums.
